fields.content: I am glad to be working with you! I was read about your company and what you are hoping to do over the course of the week. I have some ideas already, but I would like to talk to you about specifics. I am happy to set up a zoom call or talk via phone.

Feel free to send the ideas my way and I can provide any notes I have via chat. Since I'm working on launching the business and chatting with clients, I don't have much time to jump on a call. Hope that works!
In order to facilitate content I would need access to the instagram login. Or I can send you a draft version though here before I post it.
I opted out of having you post when I filled out my job posting. I'm just hoping to get the content so I can post when the time comes and the product is ready.
Let me know if that works!
No worries that works! Apparently the job details I received did not include some of this information. Thank you for the clarification.

No problem! Feel free to just send here or via email (whatever works best) when it's ready. My hope is we will be ready to start making posts in the next 2 weeks, but wanted to have the stuff just ready so all I need to do is copy/paste/upload when the time is right

Hi Vanessa. I can send you individual content (posts along with the caption), but this would mean that you have to go into this chat, find select each piece of content, copy it and transfer the image to the platform of your choice

If you would like, I could get access to your instagram account and save each post (combined with the caption), as drafts. This way you would be able to see them easily in the platform where you would post it and make any adjustments you might have. By saving them as a draft, you can post them whenever you would like and find them easily on your account.
Please let me know how you would like to proceed. Thank you!
I think sending through here works fine for me. Unless for some reason it's harder on your end. That was what I was expecting going into it so it's fine
Due to an issue with the chat I am unable to send the image. You can access the content as i upload it into the dropbox folder at the link above.
Would you like a post for one of the next few days? For anyone who might be interested in early access.
Hello, sorry was offline this weekend. For now, not going to be doing any posts since it's still so early. The early access program will also likely last for a while
I downloaded the post that was in the Dropbox! Thanks!
Ok great ill be uploading more soon
Feel free to make any edits to captions or let me know what to focus on. Thank you!
I have completed the content and uploaded them to the Dropbox folder. If you have any questions or feedback feel free to let me know. Thank you!

fields.service_description: I have an online tutoring business and I want to increase my clientele. I want to spread more fliers about my tutoring services and I also want to show off my skills of being a public speaker focusing on topics like holistic health, spiritual growth and my view of the world through the lens of science and spirituality. The times I prefer posting is around 12pm-1pm and 6-8pm, but if you guys know better times I will go with that. Resources that can be used are pictures that I can provide, quotes and memes speaking positively about spirituality, relationships, self-love/self-care, business tips, and who we are as humans. I would like to talk to the manager to explain my vision more in detail.

My website is itsperfection.co. There is a password to access since we haven't launched. Password is "Inclusive2020".I am looking to launch my business soon and want some content for my social media to help create the brand as a thought leader in the diversity & inclusion space.  I want to highlight important statistics and provide guidance for companies/employees on D&I, racism, sexism, etc. in the workplace. Some articles I've been using to guide the product can be found on our website at itsperfection.co/research. There are some accounts on Instagram that posts some good content, including "grnwdx" "edlyft" "afrotech" "thelionsstory" "pocintech" "harvard_business_review".I don't have any of my own photos for Instagram so whatever you can find that can be shared would be helpful. However, I don't want to make anyone feel like I'm stealing their content though. I'm not 100% sure about the etiquette of re-posting. You can also maybe can find some stock images or illustrations on Google of people in the workplace that are usable. @pocintech reposts others a lot, so might not be a problem!Currently I only have Instagram and LinkedIn. Will likely be setting up a Twitter but not created at the moment. Will hopefully take whatever content and re-post on those other platforms.

The intention of the NoBAWC Cooperative Support campaign is to spotlight our members/partners and provide publicity for them to get support during COVID-19. We would like to have a basic template created that has space for a photo of the logo and/or team photo, the name of the coop, the type of business industry, a fun fact (black owned business, LGBT+ business, women owned, etc.), and how people can support them during this time. In addition, we would like posts that educate the public on cooperatives (ex: the 7 cooperative values, why join a coop?, reposts from other coops: @ebprec, Sustainable Economies Law Center @selc, @usfwc, @manelagrocery, & @repaired.nations). We would like to grow our followers by at least 200 new people.

This job is going to be a test run. We are using one of our private accounts because we just want to see the functionality of iblinkco so we can get a full understanding of how it works. This account belongs to the executive assistants at NihaLife so the type of content we want posted would be anything that showcases what its like to be an executive assistant and any financial resources for young people who are looking for a better way to manage their finances or anyone who is interested in working in the finance industry. Posts can be made at any time between 10 am and 4 pm. If you have any questions please feel free to email me at simran.kaur@nihalife.com and I will get back to you as soon as possible. Thank you!

The Network of Bay Area Worker Cooperatives or NoBAWC is a grassroots organization of democratic workplaces dedicated to building workplace democracy in the San Francisco Bay Area and beyond. NoBAWC is comprised primarily of worker cooperatives.

In addition to worker cooperatives, NoBAWC includes many Bay Area workplaces that incorporate democratic principles even though they do not totally satisfy the above definition of a worker cooperative. These include workplaces in transition toward becoming worker cooperatives and those that are democratically run but not worker-owned. This latter category includes consumer cooperatives and non-profits that are democratically run by their staffs.
